Review Text: It's a quaint underrated palace in jaybheri enclave. I loved their decor and service the most. The lunch is open all day that makes it ideal for people who like to laze around in weekends. We were offered the crispy corn which was one of the best dishes. The panner butter masala was a tad bit sweet. They have Chinese and Indian dishes for lunch and their tandoor opens at night so that is a heads up if u are looking for kebabs. Definitely revisit.
The food was tasty and there were good varieties. The pulav was very different with very good aromas. Their various starters is a must try as each starter has a unique taste.
Don't expect much out of the ambience. The food is above average, and the service is good too. We went there because it was open till late at night
